It turns out that this already partially works, it's just that it does not set the end date and time properly (and as a result we see #944 at play here too), but it _does_ set the start time & date correctly:

![GNOME_Calendar_issue_278_-_convert_from_all-day_to_time-based_with_drag-and-drop](/uploads/67c4463b103584b4949fb37beeac176e/GNOME_Calendar_issue_278_-_convert_from_all-day_to_time-based_with_drag-and-drop.mp4){width=400px}

…so presumably, a newcomer could fix this without too much difficulty.

As:
* There has been no response to my requests for information over the past year;
* There is no way for me to test (as I don't have Apple accounts and devices);
* It is presumed to be working better nowadays due to bugfixes everywhere in the past two years;
* If it still happens, it might not be a bug in GNOME Calendar, but possibly in another component instead

…I am closing this ticket for now, because there is unfortunately nothing I can do on my side.

